description: Triangle T(n,k) of n X n binary matrices with k=0...n^2 ones up to row and column permutations.
example: [1, 1], [1, 1, 3, 1, 1], [1, 1, 3, 6, 7, 7, 6, 3, 1, 1] (the last block giving the numbers of 3 X 3 binary matrices with k=0...9 ones up to row and column permutations).
author: _Vladeta Jovovic_, Mar 08 2000
